'''''Spitfire 40''''' is a [[Combat flight simulation game|combat flight simulation]] video game developed by Novotrade and published by [[Mirrorsoft]] for the [[Commodore 64]] in 1985.

==Gameplay==
The game is set during the [[Battle of Britain]] where the player flies a [[Supermarine Spitfire]].<ref name="SU"/> The game features two separate screens: The view from the cockpit and the instrument panel. Both have to be used in conjunction to fly the plane. Two [[Tutorial (video games)|tutorial]] modes are included: flying practice and combat practice.<ref name="amtix"/>

